ART 55 MATTERS ARISING UNDER THE TRUSTEE ACT 1925 [rr 55.1&#x2013;55.14]"><leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.PT55.D2"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="division" searchtype="LEGISLATION DIVISION" subdoc="false" toc-caption="DIVISION 2 NEW TRUSTEES [rr 55.5&#x2013;55.7]">
<leg:heading><desig searchtype="DIV-NUM"><designum><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.PT55.D2" type="ext"/>DIVISION 2</designum></desig><title searchtype="DIV-TITLE">NEW TRUSTEES [rr 55.5&#x2013;55.7]</title></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R55-5"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="rul" searchtype="LEGISLATION RUL" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[r 55.5] r 55.5 Application (cf SCR Part 70, rule 7)">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R55-5" type="ext"/>[r 55.5]</edpnum><title searchtype="RUL-TITLE">Application (cf SCR Part 70, rule 7)</title><desig searchtype="RUL-NUM"><designum>55.5</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>This Division applies to an application for the appointment of a new trustee under Part 3 of the Trustee Act 1925 (a <defterm><emph typestyle="bf">Part 3 application</emph></defterm>).</text></p>
<leg:comntry subdoc="true" toc-caption="NOTE"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><title><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.PT55.R5.COM1" type="ext"/>NOTE</title></heading>
<level id="UCPN_UCPR.SGM_UCPN.UCPR.55-5-5" leveltype="para0" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[55.5.5] Introductory note"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.55-5-5" type="ext"/>[55.5.5] </edpnum><title>Introductory note</title></heading>
<bodytext searchtype="COMMENTARY">
<p>
<text>Part 3 of the Trustee Act 1925 (and particularly sÂ 70) confers on the court, in addition to its inherent jurisdiction, an extensive jurisdiction to appoint new trustees.</text></p>
<p>
<text>The application is usually made by summons, supported by affidavits. A summons, in addition to an order for the appointment of trustees, should seek orders vesting trust property in them.</text></p>
<p>
<text>The court will not normally exercise its power to appoint trustees where an appointment could be made out of court. The court will not, in the absence of special circumstances, appoint as a trustee: a beneficiary; a near relative or solicitor of a beneficiary; a near relative or partner of a trustee; a person out of the jurisdiction; or a foreign corporation. Despite removal of earlier restrictions, the court might ordinarily decline to appoint a corporation as trustee.</text></p>
<p>
<text>For discussions on law and procedure see A G Nevill and A W Ashe, <emph typestyle="it">Equity Proceedings with Precedents</emph> (NSW), Butterworths, Sydney, 1981 at [1211]&#x2013;[1215]; see also J D Heydon and M J Leeming, <emph typestyle="it">Jacob's Law of Trusts in Australia</emph>, 7th ed, LexisNexis Butterworths, Sydney, 2006, at [1546] and following; and Parker, <emph typestyle="it">Practice in Equity</emph>, 2nd ed, 1949, pp 758&#x2013;61, 303&#x2013;5. For a specimen form of summons, consent to act as trustee, and affidavits, see Precedents 12(6)&#x2013;12(12) in Nevill and Ashe, above.</text></p>
</bodytext>
</level></leg:comntry>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R55-6"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="rul" searchtype="LEGISLATION RUL" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[r 55.6] r 55.6 Evidence generally (cf SCR Part 70, rule 8)">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R55-6" type="ext"/>[r 55.6]</edpnum><title searchtype="RUL-TITLE">Evidence generally (cf SCR Part 70, rule 8)</title><desig searchtype="RUL-NUM"><designum>55.6</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>The evidence in support of a Part 3 application must show each of the following:</text></p>
<l><li id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R55-6..A"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R55-6..A" type="ext"/>(a)</lilabel>
<p><text>the nature of the trusts still subsisting,</text></p>
</li>
<li id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R55-6..B"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R55-6..B" type="ext"/>(b)</lilabel>
<p><text>the nature and value of the trust property,</text></p>
</li>
<li id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R55-6..C"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R55-6..C" type="ext"/>(c)</lilabel>
<p><text>whether any and, if so, what part of the trust property is subject to the Real Property Act 1900,</text></p>
</li>
<li id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R55-6..D"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R55-6..D" type="ext"/>(d)</lilabel>
<p><text>the person beneficially entitled,</text></p>
</li>
<li id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R55-6..E"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R55-6..E" type="ext"/>(e)</lilabel>
<p><text>the fitness of the proposed new trustee,</text></p>
</li>
<li id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R55-6..F"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R55-6..F" type="ext"/>(f)</lilabel>
<p><text>the consent of the proposed new trustee.</text></p>
</li>
</l>
<leg:comntry subdoc="true" toc-caption="NOTE"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><title><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.PT55.R6.COM1" type="ext"/>NOTE</title></heading>
<level id="UCPN_UCPR.SGM_UCPN.UCPR.55-6-5" leveltype="para0" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[55.6.5] Assistance of the court"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.55-6-5" type="ext"/>[55.6.5] </edpnum><title>Assistance of the court</title></heading>
<bodytext searchtype="COMMENTARY">
<p>
<text>The evidence should also show that it is inexpedient, difficult or impractical to make the appointment without the assistance of the court.</text></p>
</bodytext>
</level></leg:comntry>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R55-7"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="rul" searchtype="LEGISLATION RUL" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[r 55.7] r 55.7 Fitness of new trustee (cf SCR Part 70, rule 9)">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R55-7" type="ext"/>[r 55.7]</edpnum><title searchtype="RUL-TITLE">Fitness of new trustee (cf SCR Part 70, rule 9)</title><desig searchtype="RUL-NUM"><designum>55.7</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R55-7.1"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R55-7.1" type="ext"/>(1)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>Only one affidavit of the fitness of a proposed new trustee may be required, unless the Supreme Court otherwise orders.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R55-7.2"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R55-7.2" type="ext"/>(2)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>The affidavit must set out the following:</text></p>
<l><li id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R55-7.1.A"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R55-7.1.A" type="ext"/>(a)</lilabel>
<p><text>the proposed new trustee&#x2019;s position in life,</text></p>
</li>
<li id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R55-7.1.B"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R55-7.1.B" type="ext"/>(b)</lilabel>
<p><text>how long the deponent has known the proposed new trustee,</text></p>
</li>
<li id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R55-7.1.C"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R55-7.1.C" type="ext"/>(c)</lilabel>
<p><text>that the proposed new trustee is, to the knowledge of the deponent, of good credit,</text></p>
</li>
<li id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R55-7.1.D"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R55-7.1.D" type="ext"/>(d)</lilabel>
<p><text>that the proposed new trustee is, to the best of the information and belief of the deponent, of good character, repute and business habits.</text></p>
</li>
</l>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:bodytext>
<leg:comntry subdoc="true" toc-caption="NOTE"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><title><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.PT55.R7.COM1" type="ext"/>NOTE</title></heading>
<level id="UCPN_UCPR.SGM_UCPN.UCPR.55-7-5" leveltype="para0" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[55.7.5] Forms"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.55-7-5" type="ext"/>[55.7.5] </edpnum><title>Forms</title></heading>
<bodytext searchtype="COMMENTARY">
<p>
<text>For forms see Precedent 10(19) in A G Nevill and A W Ashe, <emph typestyle="it">Equity Proceedings with Precedents</emph> (NSW), Butterworths, Sydney, 1981.</text></p>
</bodytext>
</level></leg:comntry>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
